  "prompt": "What is Google Penguin?",
  "response": "Google Penguin is an algorithm update introduced by Google in April 2012. The primary aim of Google Penguin is to decrease the search engine rankings of websites that violate Google's Webmaster Guidelines by using black-hat SEO techniques, such as keyword stuffing, link schemes, and other manipulative tactics intended to artificially boost a site's ranking. The update was designed to ensure that high-quality, relevant content is rewarded with better search visibility, while sites engaging in unethical practices are penalized.\n\nThe Penguin update has undergone several iterations since its initial release, each refining its ability to detect and penalize websites engaging in SEO practices that violate Google's rules. In September 2016, Google announced that Penguin would become part of its core algorithm, running in real-time and affecting search rankings faster than before.",
